<ol>
<li>If no IP on the device associated with the line, BAU Cancel line</li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">If there is IP on the device</span>
<ol>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Tra=
nsfer of installment plan to different CTN under the same BAN or different =
BAN? This is out of scope and requested epic owner to update the capability=
</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">ESPR (estate settle phone return) pr=
ocess is used to cancel CTN due to death</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">If IP exists and estate/customer int=
end to return the device, BRE cancel line solution is going to be leveraged=
 to get the device back with following exceptions</span>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">ESPR specific reason code needs to b=
e used. All reason codes are defined in C1</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">If device returned is damaged, custo=
mer will NOT be charged with damage fee - reason code driven logic</span></=
li>
</ol></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">If IP exists and estate/customer can=
't return the device</span>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Cancel request from ACC should inclu=
de appropriate reason code</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">ODS receives the cancel request from=
 ACC and submits cease line request to BSSe-OC</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">BSSe-OC publishes product order to O=
CE/OG</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">OCE goes thru the cancel line automa=
tion. In addition, it calls DLC to mark the device as lost. Also calls ILS =
to write-off the loan. I presume this is again reason code driven.<span>&nb=
sp;</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">The balance on the loan is written o=
ff. Balance includes both unbilled and billed amount.</span></li>
</ol></li>
</ol></li>
</ol></td>
